The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                Four persons were injured in three mishaps late on Thursday and Friday. A 20-year-old youth was injured after he fell off a private bus on CIT Road late on Thursday. Arijit Dutta was admitted to NRS hospital. On Friday morning, an unidentified vehicle knocked down motorcyclist Shamshed Alam while he was taking a right turn from Kidderpore Road to Outram Road. He suffered serious head injuries and had to be admitted to SSKM Hospital. In the third mishap, motorcyclist Shakil Khan and pillion rider Firoz Ahmed were injured after being hit by an Ambassador on Strand Road on Friday morning. The two were taken to hospital and discharged after treatment.    A 32-year-old man, Tapan Hazra, was arrested near Prachi cinema in Sealdah on Thursday night. Police said a country-made single shot was found on the resident of Goardah in Canning.    About 300 members and supporters of the Trinamul Congress organised a procession on Friday in Salt Lake and submitted a memorandum to the sub-divisional officer, Asok Das.  ops said the party supporters met the SDO and enquired about the number of trees felled in the township for the construction of East West Metro and the rehabilitation of the Duttabad residents who would be removed for the construction. The official asked for a weeks time to assess the entire situation.    IIT, Guwahati, will conduct an all India preliminary examination on July 19 to select students for Technothlon. In Calcutta, the exam will be held at Vidya Niketan High School in Bansdroni. Those who will participate in the event will get to visit IIT laboratories and attend workshops, exhibitions and lectures by noble laureates.    The woman who had knocked down a 46-year-old man while learning to drive in Howrah on Thursday was granted bail after she surrendered before the chief judicial magistrates court in Howrah on Friday.                                                                                                                                                                   
